title: rppo vignette
text: ppo_data function queries PPO Data Portal, passing values database extracting matching results. results ppo_data function returned list five elements: 1) data frame containing data, 2) readme string containing usage information statistics query , 3) citation string containing information proper citation, 4) number_possible integer indicating total number results limit specified, 5) status code returned service. “df” variable populated results data element results list, example slice data showing first record. readme citation files returned list results can accessed calling readme citation elements. Note file “citation_and_data_use_policies.txt” referred readme file can accessed using cat(results$citation) results lists also shows number possible results results set, useful submitted query limit. example, query , limit set 10 want know many records possible limit set.
code: results <- ppo_data(genus = "Quercus", fromYear = 2013, toYear = 2013, fromDay = 100, toDay = 110, termID = 'obo:PPO_0002313', limit = 10, timeLimit = 2) df <- results$data print(df[1:1,]) #>   dayOfYear year   genus specificEpithet eventRemarks latitude longitude #> 1       101 2013 Quercus       douglasii       Leaves 37.98884 -122.1296 #>                                                                                                            termID #> 1 obo:PPO_0002313,obo:PPO_0002312,obo:PPO_0002315,obo:PPO_0002000,obo:PPO_0002014,obo:PPO_0002017,obo:PPO_0002015 #>    source                                  eventId #> 1 USA-NPN urn:phenologicalObservingProcess/4578221 cat(results$readme) #> The following contains information about your download from the Global Plant  #> Phenology Database.  Please refer to the citation_and_data_use_policies.txt  #> file for important information about data usage policies, licensing, and  #> citation protocols for each dataset.  This file contains summary information  #> about the query that was run.   #>  #> data file = data.csv #> date query ran = Mon Jan 31 2022 15:08:45 GMT+0000 (Coordinated Universal Time) #> query = +genus:Quercus AND +plantStructurePresenceTypes:"http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PPO_0002313" AND +year:>=2013 AND +year:<=2013 AND +dayOfYear:>=100 AND +dayOfYear:<=110 AND source:USA-NPN #> fields returned = dayOfYear,year,genus,specificEpithet,eventRemarks,latitude,longitude,source,eventId #> user specified limit = 10 #> total results possible = 518 #> total results returned = 10 cat(results$number_possible) #> 518

what: working with terms and data together
title: rppo vignette
text: generate data frame showing frequency “present” “absent” terms particular query. query genus = “Quercus” latitude > 47. row returned data frame ppo_data typically return multiple terms termID field, corresponding phenological stages defined PPO. example, generate frequency table number times “present” “absent” term occur entire returned dataset. Note termID field returned ppo_data return “presence” terms addition “present” “absent” terms, ppo_terms function returns “present” “absent” terms. Thus, frequency distribution counts number “present” “absent” terms [-depth discussion difference “presence”, “present”, “absent”, see https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fpls.2018.00517/full]. Finally, since termIDs returned URI identifiers easily readable text, example maps termIDs labels. resulting data frame shows two columns: 1) column term labels, 2) frequency number times label appeared result set.
code: ############################################################################### # Generate a frequency data frame showing the number of times each termID # is populated for genus equals "Quercus" above latitude of 47 # Note that all latitude/longitude queries need to be in the format of a # bounding box ############################################################################### df <- ppo_data(   genus = "Quercus",    limit="10", timeLimit = 4) #> sending request for data ... #> https://www.plantphenology.org/api/v3/download/_search?q=%2Bgenus:Quercus+AND+source:USA-NPN&source=latitude,longitude,year,dayOfYear,termID&limit=10 # return just the termID column t1 <- df$data[,c('termID')] # paste each cell into one string t2<-paste(t1, collapse = ",") # split strings at , t3<-strsplit(t2, ",") # create a frequency table as a data frame freqFrame <- as.data.frame(table(t3))  # create a new data frame that we want to populate resultFrame <- data.frame(   label = character(),    frequency = integer(),    stringsAsFactors = FALSE)  ############################################################################### # Replace termIDs with labels in frequency frame ############################################################################### # fetch "present" and "absent" terms using `ppo_terms` termList <- ppo_terms(absent = TRUE, present = TRUE, timeLimit = 2); #> sending request for terms ... #> No encoding supplied: defaulting to UTF-8.  # loop all "present"" and "absent" terms if (!is.null(termList)) {   for (term in 1:nrow(termList)) {     termListTermID<-termList[term,'termID'];     termListLabel<-termList[term,'label'];     # loop all rows that have a frequency generated     for (row in 1:nrow(freqFrame)) {       freqFrameTermID = freqFrame[row,'t3']       freqFrameFrequency = freqFrame[row,'Freq']       # Populate resultFrame with matching "present" or "absent" labels.       # In this step, we will ignore "presence" terms       # found in the frequency frame since the ppo_terms only returns       # "present" and "absent" terms.        if (freqFrameTermID == termListTermID) {         resultFrame[nrow(resultFrame)+1,] <- c(termListLabel,freqFrameFrequency)       }     }   } } else {   message("termList is null, likely due to a server response issue.  Try increasing the timeLimit or try again later. If the problem persists email the authors.") }   # print results, showing term labels and a frequency count print(resultFrame) #>                                                 label frequency #> 1                           breaking leaf buds absent         2 #> 2                          breaking leaf buds present         8 #> 3                       expanding true leaves present         8 #> 4                                   leaf buds present         8 #> 5  new above-ground shoot-borne shoot systems present         8 #> 6                            new shoot system present         8 #> 7                       non-dormant leaf buds present         8 #> 8                                 true leaves present         8 #> 9                       unfolding true leaves present         8 #> 10                            vascular leaves present         8

title: Access the Global Plant Phenology Data Portal
text: global plant phenology data portal, aggregation plant phenological observations USA-NPN, NEON, PEP725 representing 20 million phenological observations across North America Europe. PPO data portal utilizes Plant Phenology Ontology (PPO) align phenological terms measurements various databases. rppo R package enables programmatic access data contained PPO data portal incuding selected classes contained PPO . information data assembled PPO data portal, visit ppo-data-pipeline git repository.

title: Access Data From the Global Plant Phenology Data Portal — ppo_data
text: scientificName (character) plant species scientific name. genus (character) plant genus name. See details. specificEpithet (character) plant specific epithet termID (character) single termID plant phenology ontology. See details. fromYear (integer) return data specified year toYear (integer) return data including specified year fromDay (integer) return data starting specified day toDay (integer) return data including specified day bbox (character) return data within bounding box. Format lat,long,lat,long structured string.  Use website: http://boundingbox.klokantech.com/ quickly grab bbox (set format bottom left csv sure switch order long, lat, long, lat lat, long, lat, long). source (character) return data specified source. See details. subSource (character) return data specified sub-source. See details. status (character) Either "present" "absent". Return data specified status. mapped_traits (character) return data specified traits. See details eventRemarks (character) return data specified eventRemarks limit (integer) limit returned data specified number records timeLimit (integer) set limit amount time wait response keepData (logical) whether keep (TRUE) delete (FALSE; default) downloaded data (~/ppo_download/).

title: Access Data From the Global Plant Phenology Data Portal — ppo_data
text: list following elements: `data`: data frame containing data `readme`: string information return package `citation`: string citation information `number_possible`: integer total possible results `status_code`: integer status code returned server

title: Access Data From the Global Plant Phenology Data Portal — ppo_data
text: ppo_data function returns list containing following information: readme file, citation information, data frame data, integer number records returned status code. function called parameters correspond values contained data act filter returned record set. list available mapped_traits, termID, Source subSource see ppo_filters dataset. mapped_traits termID, ppo_get_terms function return data.frame present, absent terms traits information. ppo_terms use API get lastest data. However, traits/termID may return results function. See documentation details.

title: Access the Global Plant Phenology Data Portal — rppo-package
text: rppo enables users query global plant phenology data portal (PPO data portal). PPO data portal aggregation phenology data several different data sources.  Currently contains USA-NPN, NEON, PEP725 data sources.  PPO data portal harvests data using ppo-data-pipeline, code available https://github.com/biocodellc/ppo-data-pipeline/.  phenological terms data portal aligned using Plant Phenology Ontology (PPO), available https://github.com/PlantPhenoOntology/ppo. Three main functions contained rppo: ppo_terms allows users discover present absent phenological stages, ppo_data enables users query PPO data portal ppo_traits use data fetched PPO data portal return traits data eventID. rppo package source code available https://github.com/ropensci/rppo/.
